U.S. is hoping to reopen the country after a record 22 million unemployed as of April 17 [1] , wiping out a decade of job gains, but still, experts in U.S still strongly against reopening the country until at least May 20. [2] And even when the curve is flatten after immense team efforts from the community, they will still be fears that a second wave of outbreak might betide upon us. South Korean had recently reported a scary reports that find 163 people who recovered from coronavirus have
retested positive [3], making the situation even more alarming.

